friend Eugène Delacroix.

4
00:00:15.948 --> 00:00:20.504
In his day, Chopin was called the poet of
the piano, and he wrote exclusively for

5
00:00:20.504 --> 00:00:21.900
the piano.

6
00:00:21.900 --> 00:00:26.000
No purely instrumental works,
other than those for the piano, or

7
00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:29.741
that involve the piano one way or
another as a accompanied instrument.

8
00:00:31.050 --> 00:00:35.510
Chopin was Polish by birth, but
his father was french, a french citizen.

9
00:00:35.510 --> 00:00:40.470
And Chopin himself spent almost
all of his adult life in Paris.

10
00:00:40.470 --> 00:00:45.206
In the end living comfortably
in an apartment on the trendy

11
00:00:45.206 --> 00:00:50.244
Place Vendôme across from where
the Ritz Hotel stands today.

12
00:00:50.244 --> 00:00:55.049
And in this apartment,
Chopin died in 1849 at the age of just 39.

13
00:00:55.049 --> 00:00:59.980
Chopin was slight of frame and
weak of constitution.

14
00:00:59.980 --> 00:01:02.320
He actually died of tuberculosis.

15
00:01:02.320 --> 00:01:06.958
And unlike his friend Franz Liszt,
Chopin much preferred

16
