Chopin's favored instrument was
a Pleyel piano, as we've seen.

19
00:01:21.850 --> 00:01:24.480
Made by the firm of Camille Pleyel.

20
00:01:24.480 --> 00:01:25.950
This one constructed in 1842.

21
00:01:25.950 --> 00:01:33.730
To the right, you see an actual photograph
of Chopin, taken in his last year, 1849.

22
00:01:33.730 --> 00:01:36.200
A sickly figure.

23
00:01:36.200 --> 00:01:39.770
As to what Chopin wrote for,
and played on the piano,

24
00:01:39.770 --> 00:01:43.430
well, Nocturnes, Etudes, Preludes.

25
00:01:43.430 --> 00:01:48.540
We heard Robert Blocker play,
Chopin's Prelude in C minor.

26
00:01:48.540 --> 00:01:53.000
Music with a Polish national or
nationalistic flavor, Mazurkas and

27
